      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "*Insert obligatory \"Sorry if this was really obvious...\" here.*\n\nWhen placing mimcaps in layout, we have the option for mimcap option MIM-A or MIM-B, and also the option to choose which layers we place between.\n\n[This post](https://discord.com/channels/1361349522684510449/1444137681712971898/1444236820249317426) seems to suggest that we should use MIM-B between M4-M5 (on top of M4).\n\n* Is MIM-B with M4-M5 the only MIM configuration we're allowed to use? What others can we use, if any?\n\nThe docs page [referenced](https://gf180mcu-pdk.readthedocs.io/en/latest/analog/layout/inter_specs/inter_specs_3_43.html) in the above message suggests there are two possibilities for the SiN thickness, which lead to different capacitances.\n\n* What is the SiN thickness used in waferspace gf180mcu?\n\nThanks.",
      "author": {
        "id": "325334453213986816",
        "name": "were491.",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "were491",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [],
        "avatarUrl": "2026-06_media/35aa2f7ec1a538a595dd72ef98e360e0-BF0F0.png"
      },
