      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "For now, the best way to get that information is to read the magic techfile for gf180mcuD.\n\n> **Note that there are multiple mutually exclusive process options for the\n>  high sheet rho resistor and MiM capacitor.  This tech file assumes the\n>  options 1kOhm/sq for the resistor and 2fF/um for the MiM capacitor.\n\nHowever, this is a surprise to me, since I would have expected 1.5fF/um2 or 1.0fF/um2.\n\nThe device is called cap_mim_2f0_m4m5_noshield, which would also suggest 2fF, but I don't even see that option the in the stackup?\n\nThe only place I can find 2.0fF in the documentation is on this page, which shows strange model names for the MIM caps: https://gf180mcu-pdk.readthedocs.io/en/latest/analog/model_parameters/LV/LV_1_4_6.html\nIt seems to incorrectly use the model names from the MOSCAP models: https://gf180mcu-pdk.readthedocs.io/en/latest/analog/model_parameters/LV/LV_1_4_5.html\n\n@Tim Edwards do you have any idea what's going on here?",
      "author": {
        "id": "323371864074485771",
        "name": "mole99",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Leo Moser (mole99)",
