    {
      "id": "1511635089875009537",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-06-03T07:38:10.248+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "So the \"A\" in tha test might refer to option `a` on that page which is indeed 1.5 f/F.\nNow why doesn't that match the option we think we have and the min/max value ... I'm starting to think the labels have been cut or only reflect the first option or somethign which would also explain why the label mention 9K top metal while we should have 11 K one.",
      "author": {
        "id": "596068704471482370",
        "name": "246tnt",
