      "content": "Thanks, I totally missed that scrolling through/grepping for things I thought would match. Based on the defined subckts from `gf180mcuD/libs.tech/ngspice/sm141064_mim.ngspice` (the path as in IIC-OSIC-TOOLS), it seems the documentation is incorrect here. ('documentation' referring to the stackup page: https://gf180mcu-pdk.readthedocs.io/en/latest/analog/layout/inter_specs/inter_specs_3_43.html)\n\nSo, I assume in layout (KLayout) I can use cap_mim with MIM-B and M4-M5 options selected, but expect the final capacitance to be ~2.0fF/um^2 for simulation purposes. Is this correct?",
      "author": {
